### Step 12 — Monitor (`src/monitor.ts`)

```typescript
export async function monitorPulseBoardProvider(opts: {
  accountId?: string;
  config?: CoreConfig;
  runtime?: RuntimeEnv;
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
  statusSink?: (patch: { lastInboundAt?: number }) => void;
}): Promise<{ stop: () => void }>
```

Since PulseBoard is fictional, the monitor uses a polling loop (500ms interval)
that checks `abortSignal.aborted` and resolves when signaled. In a real
implementation this would open a WebSocket to the PulseBoard push endpoint.
The polling stub serves as a structural placeholder that tests can override.

